1. Using color names example:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>HTML Colors Application</title>
    </head>
    <body text="pink" bgcolor="grey">
        <h3>HTML Colors Application</h3>
        <table bgcolor="blue">
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Hello YouTubers, welcome to software developer channel!<br />
                    Here you learn free tutorials in programming.
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </body>
</html>

2. Using rgb values example:

<body text="rgb(255,0,255)" bgcolor="rgb(192,192,192)">
        <h3>HTML Colors Application</h3>
        <table bgcolor="rgb(0,0,255)">
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Hello YouTubers, welcome to software developer channel!<br />
                    Here you learn free tutorials in programming.
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </body>

3. Using Hexadecimal code example:

<body text="#ff00ff" bgcolor="#808080">
        <h3>HTML Colors Application</h3>
        <table bgcolor="#0000ff">
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Hello YouTubers, welcome to software developer channel!<br />
                    Here you learn free tutorials in programming.
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </body>
